## Phase 1 — Navigation Overhaul

**Goal**: Replace the always-present sidebar with a bottom tab bar on small screens. On `md:`
and above, everything looks and works exactly as today. No changes to routing, API calls, or
page components.

### Files to create

#### `src/ui/web/src/components/BottomNav.tsx`

A fixed bottom bar (`fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0`) rendered only on screens narrower than `md:`.
Uses `pb-safe` (Tailwind safe-area plugin) for iPhone home indicator.

Structure:
```tsx
<nav className="fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 z-40 flex border-t border-gray-800
                bg-gray-950 pb-safe md:hidden">
  {/* z-40 — sits above page content but below the z-50 drawer and its backdrop */}
  {tabs.map(tab => (
    <NavLink
      key={tab.to}
      to={tab.to}
      className={({ isActive }) =>
        `flex flex-1 flex-col items-center gap-1 py-3 text-xs
         ${isActive ? "text-indigo-400" : "text-gray-400"}`
      }
    >
      <tab.Icon className="h-5 w-5" />
      {tab.label}
    </NavLink>
  ))}
</nav>
```

Tabs array is built from current route params: `libraryId` from `useParams()`. Browse and
Settings tabs include `libraryId` in their `to` path and are rendered conditionally (hidden,
not disabled, when no library is active — they simply don't appear in `tabs` if `!libraryId`).

#### `src/ui/web/src/components/DrawerOverlay.tsx`

Reusable slide-over wrapper. Accepts `open`, `onClose`, and `children`. Renders:
- A fixed full-screen semi-transparent backdrop (`bg-black/50 z-50`) that calls `onClose`
  on click.
- A fixed full-height panel (`z-50`) that slides in from the left (`translate-x-0` when open,
  `-translate-x-full` when closed), `transition-transform duration-200`.

**Stacking order**: `BottomNav` is `z-40`; `DrawerOverlay` (backdrop + panel) is `z-50`.
This ensures the open drawer sits above the bottom bar, preventing the nav from stealing taps
through the backdrop. While the drawer is open the bottom bar is visually covered.

**Accessibility note**: For a first pass the drawer is pointer/touch only. A follow-up should
add a focus trap (e.g. `focus-trap-react`), `Escape` key to close, and restore focus to the
menu button on close. Defer explicitly rather than leaving it unaddressed.

```tsx
interface DrawerOverlayProps {
  open: boolean;
  onClose: () => void;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}
```

### Files to modify

#### `src/ui/web/src/components/AppShell.tsx`

Add `BottomNav` below `<Outlet />`. Add `pb-16 md:pb-0` to `<main>` so page content is not
obscured by the bottom bar on mobile.

Change the outer flex container to hide the sidebar `<div>` below `md:`:

```tsx
// Before
<div className={`${sidebarWidth} transition-all duration-200`}>
  <Sidebar ... />
</div>

// After
<div className={`hidden md:block ${sidebarWidth} transition-all duration-200`}>
  <Sidebar ... />
</div>
```

The sidebar component itself is unchanged. On mobile it simply does not render.

#### `src/ui/web/src/pages/BrowsePage.tsx`

The in-page directory tree sidebar currently lives inside the BrowsePage layout. Wrap its
container div with `DrawerOverlay` on mobile and a standard side column on `md:`. Add a
`drawerOpen` state (default `false`) and a menu button in the page header that sets it.

Header addition (mobile only):
```tsx
<button
  className="md:hidden p-2 -ml-2 rounded-lg text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-100"
  onClick={() => setDrawerOpen(true)}
  aria-label="Open folder browser"
>
  <Bars3Icon className="h-5 w-5" />
</button>
```

#### `tailwind.config.js`

Add the `tailwindcss-safe-area` plugin to support `pb-safe` / `pt-safe`:

```js
import safeArea from "tailwindcss-safe-area";

export default {
  content: ["./index.html", "./src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"],
  theme: { extend: {} },
  plugins: [safeArea],
};
```

Add `tailwindcss-safe-area` to `package.json` devDependencies.

### Acceptance criteria

- On a 390px viewport: bottom tab bar visible, sidebar invisible, content fills full width.
- On a 768px+ viewport: sidebar visible, bottom tab bar invisible, behavior identical to today.
- BrowsePage: tapping the menu button opens the directory tree as a drawer; tapping the
  backdrop closes it.
- All existing Vitest tests pass without modification.

